@startuml sequence-stripe
title Séquence — Souscription Premium Stripe

actor User
participant "PricingPage" as UI
participant "ApiClient" as Api
participant "subscription.controller" as Ctrl
participant "stripe.service" as Svc
participant "Stripe API" as Stripe
participant "Stripe Checkout" as Checkout
database "Prisma / Neon" as DB

== 1. Création de la session ==

User -> UI : clique "Passer Premium" (monthly)
UI -> Api : POST /subscription/checkout { plan: 'monthly' }
Api -> Ctrl : request (JWT)
Ctrl -> Svc : createCheckoutSession(userId, plan)
Svc -> DB : User { stripeCustomerId? }
DB --> Svc : user

alt customer absent
  Svc -> Stripe : customers.create({ email })
  Stripe --> Svc : { id: cus_xxx }
  Svc -> DB : update User.stripeCustomerId
end

Svc -> Stripe : checkout.sessions.create\n(price, customer, trial_period_days: 14,\nsuccess_url, cancel_url)
Stripe --> Svc : { url: checkout.stripe.com/... }
Svc --> Ctrl : { url }
Ctrl --> Api : 200
Api --> UI : { url }
UI -> Checkout : window.location = url

== 2. Paiement ==

User -> Checkout : saisit CB
Checkout -> Stripe : confirm payment
Stripe --> Checkout : success
Checkout -> UI : redirect success_url\n(/dashboard?upgraded=1)

== 3. Webhook (asynchrone) ==

Stripe ->> Ctrl : POST /subscription/webhook\n(customer.subscription.created)
Ctrl -> Svc : handleWebhook(rawBody, signature)
Svc -> Svc : stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()\n→ vérifie signature HMAC
Svc -> DB : update User {\n  isPremium: true,\n  stripeSubscriptionId,\n  premiumExpiresAt\n}
DB --> Svc : ok
Svc --> Ctrl : ok
Ctrl --> Stripe : 200

== 4. UI ==

UI -> Api : GET /subscription/status
Api -> Ctrl : request
Ctrl -> Svc : getStatus(userId)
Svc -> DB : User
DB --> Svc : { isPremium: true, expiresAt }
Svc --> Ctrl : status
Ctrl --> Api : 200
Api --> UI : affiche badge Premium ★

@enduml
